[348.938699, "o", "                        [\u001b[4mARGUMENTS\u001b[24m...]\u001b[m"]
[348.938805, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 245 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 246 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       NetworkManager stores all network configuration as \"connections\", which are\u001b[m"]
[348.938896, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 247 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.057089, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.058735, "o", "       collections of data (Layer2 details, IP addressing, etc.) that describe how to\u001b[m"]
[350.059333, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 248 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       create or connect to a network. A connection is \"active\" when a device uses\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 249 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       that connection's configuration to create or connect to a network. There may\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 250 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.098189, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.09881, "o", "       be multiple connections that apply to a device, but only one of them can be\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 251 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.101111, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.101801, "o", "       active on that device at any given time. The additional connections can be\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 252 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       used to allow quick switching between different networks and configurations.\u001b[m"]
[350.102555, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 253 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.119953, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m"]
[350.120606, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 254 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.121412, "o", "       Consider a machine which is usually connected to a DHCP-enabled network, but\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 255 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       sometimes connected to a testing network which uses static IP addressing.\u001b[m\r\n"]
[350.121484, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 256 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.13977, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.140221, "o", "       Instead of manually reconfiguring eth0 each time the network is changed, the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 257 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       settings can be saved as two connections which both apply to eth0, one for\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 258 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       DHCP (called default) and one with the static addressing details (called\u001b[m"]
[350.140251, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 259 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.158157, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.158591, "o", "       testing). When connected to the DHCP-enabled network the user would run \u001b[1mnmcli\u001b[0m\u001b[m"]
[350.159125, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 260 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1mcon up default \u001b[22m, and when connected to the static network the user would run\u001b[m\r\n"]
[350.159181, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 261 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.161882, "o", "       \u001b[1mnmcli con up testing\u001b[22m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 262 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.177556, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.177658, "o", "\u001b[m"]
[350.177682, "o", "\r\n"]
[350.177706, "o", "\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 263 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.17834, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1mshow \u001b[22m[\u001b[1m--active\u001b[22m] [\u001b[1m--order \u001b[22m[+-]\u001b[4mcategory\u001b[24m:...]\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 264 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.178555, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           List in-memory and on-disk connection profiles, some of which may also be\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 265 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.2616, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           active if a device is using that connection profile. Without a parameter,\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 266 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.2623, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           all profiles are listed. When \u001b[1m--active \u001b[22moption is specified, only the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 267 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           active profiles are shown.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 268 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.730214, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 269 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           The \u001b[1m--order \u001b[22moption can be used to get custom ordering of connections. The\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 270 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           connections can be ordered by active status (active), name (name), type\u001b[m"]
[350.730654, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 271 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.751466, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           (type) or D-Bus path (path). If connections are equal according to a sort\u001b[m"]
[350.752089, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 272 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           order category, an additional category can be specified. The default\u001b[m"]
[350.752151, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 273 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           sorting order is equivalent to --order active:name:path.  + or no prefix\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 274 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.772987, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           means sorting in ascending order (alphabetically or in numbers), - means\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 275 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.773678, "o", "           reverse (descending) order. The category names can be abbreviated (e.g.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 276 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.773867, "o", "           --order -a:na).\u001b[m"]
[350.774615, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 277 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.793506, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 278 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K       \u001b[1mshow \u001b[22m[\u001b[1m--active\u001b[22m] [\u001b[1mid \u001b[22m| \u001b[1muuid \u001b[22m| \u001b[1mpath \u001b[22m| \u001b[1mapath\u001b[22m] \u001b[4mID\u001b[24m...\u001b[m"]
[350.794085, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 279 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.794281, "o", "           Show details for specified connections. By default, both static\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 280 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.815173, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.815651, "o", "           configuration and active connection data are displayed. When \u001b[1m--active\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 281 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           option is specified, only the active profiles are taken into account. Use\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 282 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.816027, "o", "           global \u001b[1m--show-secrets \u001b[22moption to display secrets associated with the\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 283 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.830497, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           profile.\u001b[m"]
[350.830852, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 284 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m"]
[350.830922, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 285 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           \u001b[1mid\u001b[22m, \u001b[1muuid\u001b[22m, \u001b[1mpath \u001b[22mand \u001b[1mapath \u001b[22mkeywords can be used if \u001b[4mID\u001b[24m is ambiguous. Optional\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 286 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.844378, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.844785, "o", "           \u001b[4mID\u001b[24m-specifying keywords are:\u001b[m"]
[350.844895, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 287 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 288 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           \u001b[1mid\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 289 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.858589, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[350.859017, "o", "               the \u001b[4mID\u001b[24m denotes a connection name.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 290 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 291 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           \u001b[1muuid\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 292 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.914742, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K               the \u001b[4mID\u001b[24m denotes a connection UUID.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 293 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[350.914994, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m"]
[350.917948, "o", "\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 294 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K           \u001b[1mpath\u001b[0m\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 295 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[351.029075, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
[351.029514, "o", "               the \u001b[4mID\u001b[24m denotes a D-Bus static connection path in the format of\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 296 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K               /org/freedesktop/NetworkManager/Settings/\u001b[4mnum\u001b[24m or just \u001b[4mnum\u001b[24m.\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 297 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K\u001b[m\r\n\u001b[7m Manual page nmcli(1) line 298 (press h for help or q to quit)\u001b[27m\u001b[K"]
[352.41732, "o", "\r\u001b[K \u001b[KESC\b\b\bESC\u001b[KO\bO\u001b[KB\bB\r\u001b[K"]
